
// The code snippet uses the [lambda2hyper] slot to create a Hyperlambda string from various system metrics and configurations. It retrieves the version, counts of persisted tasks, log items, cache items, endpoints, slots, and dynamic slots, as well as checks for socket and scheduler presence. It also fetches the default database and timezone settings, and lists the last log items and modules. The result is a comprehensive snapshot of the system's current state in Hyperlambda format.
lambda2hyper
   version:x:@version
   persisted_tasks:x:@tasks.count
   has_sockets:x:@.has-sockets
   has_scheduler:x:@.has-scheduler
   log_items:x:@log.count
   cache_items:x:@cache.count
   endpoints:x:@.no-endpoints
   slots:x:@.no-slots
   dynamic_slots:x:@.no-dynamic-slots
   default_db:x:@.default-db
   default_timezone:x:@.default-timezone
   last_log_items
   modules
